78% versus 56% at 1 year (p = 0.001), 60% versus 39% at 3 years (p = 0.004), and 
52% versus 29% at 5 years (p = 0.002). The limb salvage rate was 69% at 5 years.
CONCLUSIONS: Ectopic vein grafts with primarily arm vein are an acceptable 
alternative for infrainguinal reconstruction in the absence of suitable 
ipsilateral greater saphenous vein.

